<subSubSection id="E42356122C384FCBCBC90ADD6D9B6EAA" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3DA34D456A64E4EBB3FA1343B6340307" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B1F7CD2D03B02F848B3E04674606F61" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
Morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8A6CE2DDFAC74BD592F1187113DDF539" genus="I." lsidName="I. henryi" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="henryi">
<emphasis id="AA642219930C8942BE0FDECAC70AFE5C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">I. henryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the new species differs in having wider sepals (ca. 7 mm versus 4 mm) and style branch lobes that are shorter (ca. 2-3 mm versus 6 mm).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
